        "release_notes": {
            "en-US": "This release only includes minor UI improvements.\n\nChangelog for 1.3:\n* Tag input field now is focused when opening 'edit tags' dialog.\n* Suggestion button has shortkey in 'edit tags' dialog.\n* Added 'remove all tags' to a messages context menu and to 'message &gt; tag the bird' menu."
        },
        "reviewed": null,
        "url": "https://addons.thunderbird.net/en-US/thunderbird/addon/tag-the-bird/versions/1.3",
        "version": "1.3"
    },
    "default_locale": "en-US",
    "description": {
        "en-US": "IMPORTANT: Please see <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/c7b0b9f1d6bc65834f84925b2d1edd2fbee78c86ec61ca7f12eb1808ecff1827/http%3A//tagthebird.alexandrow.org\">http://tagthebird.alexandrow.org</a> for already submitted feature requests and bug reports before you send me another one. Please send new requests per email, for i'm quite lazy when it comes to checking the discussion board.\n\nTags are stored directly into a message's headers, so they are fully search- and forwardable.\nYou can use <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/a57d7b00b2c1bfc9aac8c43311c71114769c14b00f47cd2ec9713e4b1143b376/http%3A//tagthe.net\">http://tagthe.net</a> to auto-tag your messages via a secure connection.\nSuggestion of frequently used tags. Add them without touching the keyboard.\n3 different ways of searching and organizing tagged mail.\nYou can define an arbitrary number of external search engines (like Google or <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/fa14e1865a956374b564170429fd9a0b3d948579309783668814e70a516ed636/http%3A//del.icio.us\">del.icio.us</a>) where you can search for your tags."
    },
